quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  3,113,"Yet they are not all alike: there are some among the People of the Book who are upright, who recite God‚Äôs revelations throughout the night, prostrating ňĻin prayerňļ"
  3,114,"They believe in God and the Last Day, encourage good and forbid evil, and race with one another in doing good. They are ňĻtrulyňļ among the righteous"
  3,115,They will never be denied the reward for any good they have done. And God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of those mindful ňĻof Himňļ
  3,116,"Indeed, neither the wealth nor children of the disbelievers will be of any benefit to them against God. It is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever"
  3,117,"The good they do in this worldly life is like the harvest of an evil people struck by a bitter wind, destroying it ňĻcompletelyňļ. God never wronged them, but they wronged themselves"
  3,118,"O believers! Do not associate closely with others who would not miss a chance to harm you. Their only desire is to see you suffer. Their prejudice has become evident from what they say‚ÄĒand what their hearts hide is far worse. We have made Our revelations clear to you, if only you understood"
  3,119,"Here you are! You love them but they do not love you, and you believe in all Scriptures. When they meet you they say, ‚ÄúWe believe.‚ÄĚ But when alone, they bite their fingertips in rage. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúňĻMay youňļ die of your rage!‚ÄĚ Surely God knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart"
  3,120,"When you ňĻbelieversňļ are touched with good, they grieve; but when you are afflicted with evil, they rejoice. ňĻYet,ňļ if you are patient and mindful ňĻof Godňļ, their schemes will not harm you in the least. Surely God is Fully Aware of what they do"
  3,121,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when you left your home in the early morning to position the believers in the battlefield. And God is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  3,122,"ňĻRememberňļ when two groups among you ňĻbelieversňļ were about to cower, then God reassured them. So in God let the believers put their trust"
  3,123,"Indeed, God made you victorious at Badr when you were ňĻvastlyňļ outnumbered. So be mindful of God, perhaps you will be grateful"
  3,124,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when you said to the believers, ‚ÄúIs it not enough that your Lord will send down a reinforcement of three thousand angels for your aid?‚ÄĚ"
  3,125,"Most certainly, if you ňĻbelieversňļ are firm and mindful ňĻof Godňļ and the enemy launches a sudden attack on you, God will reinforce you with five thousand angels designated ňĻfor battleňļ"
  3,126,"God ordained this ňĻreinforcementňļ only as good news for you and reassurance for your hearts. And victory comes only from God‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise‚ÄĒ"
  3,127,"to destroy a group of the disbelievers and humble the rest, causing them to withdraw in disappointment"
  3,128,"You ňĻO Prophetňļ have no say in the matter.¬†It is up to God to turn to them in mercy or punish them, for indeed they are wrongdoers"
  3,129,"To God ňĻaloneňļ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. He forgives whoever He wills, and punishes whoever He wills. And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  3,130,"O believers! Do not consume interest, multiplying it many times over. And be mindful of God, so you may prosper"
  3,131,Guard yourselves against the Fire prepared for the disbelievers
  3,132,"Obey God and the Messenger, so you may be shown mercy"